This is my build of st-0.8.4, a simple terminal emulator for X which sucks less.
Check the log directory for the applied patches.

My builds are made in my home directory (~/.config/suckless/st).
Go to that directory and enter as user (no root):
make clean install

Make a symlink to ~/bin
'ln -s -v ~/.config/suckless/st/st ~/bin/st'

st patching
------------
1. Download a patch from suckless.org and place the patch at a set location 
   (~/Stack/suckless/st/patches/test)
2. Run from command line the .bashrc alias: stpatch

Safe as stable version
------------
Run from command line the .bashrc alias: stbackup

Restore stable version
------------
Run from command line the .bashrc alias: ststable

Run vanilla st
------------
Run from command line the .bashrc alias: stvanilla
